A man identified as Sikiru Alabi Owolabi has allegedly stabbed a 48-year-old man, Bolanle Adilewa, to death at Ijo Mimo area of Akure, the Ondo State capital. LEADERSHIP gathered that the suspect and the deceased engaged in an argument, leading to a fight and stabbing of the deceased to death. The deceased was said to be the son of the landlord of the suspect. A source told LEADERSHIP that the suspect, who is said to be a shoemaker in a shop in the deceased’s father’s house, engaged the deceased in a fight following a hot argument between them. According to the source, “As they were fighting, the shoemaker took a broken bottle and stabbed him (Adinlewa). He later gave up the ghost on the way to the hospital. Confirming the incident, the police public relations officer, Mrs Funmilayo Odunlami, said the incident happened during a free- for-all between the duo. She  said while the alleged killer was already in police custody, the matter had been transferred to the Criminal Investigative Department of the police command for further investigation. Odunlami said, “The suspect is in our custody, he said he acted in self-defence when the deceased took an object to attack him while they were fighting. We have transferred the case to the SCID for further investigation.”  